  "parent": "oc",
  "notes": "Aranese (Aranès). Gascon variety of Occitan spoken in Val d'Aran, Catalonia. ~2,800 speakers. Co-official with Catalan and Spanish in Catalonia. Hallmark Gascon features: Latin F- → [h] aspiration (fo→hòc, flor→hlòr), final -a → [ɔ], front rounded /y/ (⟨u⟩). Regulated by Conselh Generau d'Aran. Classical Occitan orthography with Gascon conventions.",
